Lightning Beat Penguins to Force Game 7 in NHL First-Round Playoff Series

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-04-26T02:03:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/lightning-beat-penguins-to-force-game-7-in-nhl-first-round-playoff-series.html
The Tampa Bay Lightning beat the
Pittsburgh Penguins 4-2 to force a decisive seventh game in
their National Hockey League first-round playoff series.  Steve Downie and Ryan Malone scored third-period goals as
the Lightning -- the fifth seed in the Eastern Conference --
snapped a 2-2 tie at St. Pete Times Forum in Tampa,  Florida .  Pittsburgh, which is the fourth seed, will host Game 7 in
the best-of-seven series on April 27.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  